  "prompt": "Can I be pregnant while having a missed period?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to be pregnant if you have a missed period. A missed period is one of the most common early signs of pregnancy, particularly if you have regular menstrual cycles. Other potential signs of pregnancy may include nausea, breast tenderness, fatigue, and frequent urination.\n\nHowever, a missed period can also be caused by a variety of other factors, including stress, significant weight changes, hormonal imbalances, certain medical conditions, or the use of contraceptives.\n\nIf you suspect you might be pregnant, the best way to confirm it is to take a home pregnancy test or consult with a healthcare professional.",
